================================================================================
KEY VFE-SURPRISE INSIGHTS
================================================================================
1. SURPRISE = -E_p[ln P(o|s)] under PRIOR beliefs
2. VFE = Complexity - Accuracy (Bayesian surprise under posterior)
3. High surprise → Unexpected observation → Large belief update
4. Complexity measures belief change: KL(posterior || prior)
5. Accuracy measures model fit: E_q[ln P(o|s)] under posterior
6. VFE minimization = Optimal Bayesian inference
7. Different priors → Different surprise → Different VFE

============================================================
INFERENCE DYNAMICS WITH VFE TRACKING
============================================================
Track how VFE components evolve during inference process.
Shows the relationship between evidence strength and VFE.

Evidence Strength vs VFE Components (Observing evidence for State 0)
================================================================================
Evidence      VFE     Complexity  Accuracy   Posterior_0  Certainty
Weak Evidence    1.050      0.007    -1.043       0.381       0.381
Moderate Evidence    1.003      0.104    -0.900       0.545       0.545
Strong Evidence    1.099      0.580    -0.518       0.850       0.850

KEY INSIGHTS:
- Stronger evidence → Lower VFE → Higher certainty
- Weak evidence → Higher VFE → Lower certainty
- Complexity increases with belief change magnitude
- Accuracy increases with evidence strength
- VFE = unified measure of inference quality

