🔍 STATE INFERENCE FOUNDATIONS:
1. State inference uses Bayes rule: P(state|obs) ∝ P(obs|state) × P(state)
2. VFE provides unified framework: VFE = Complexity - Accuracy
3. Surprise quantifies unexpectedness: Surprise = -E_p[ln P(o|s)]
4. VFE minimization = Optimal Bayesian inference
5. Perfect observations → Low VFE → High certainty
6. Evidence strength inversely relates to VFE

🚀 PYMDP AGENT INTEGRATION:
7. Agent class performs real-time state inference seamlessly
8. Multi-modal observations enable rich sensory integration
9. Multi-factor state spaces capture complex environment dynamics
10. Continuous inference provides real-time state awareness
11. Context-dependent observation models adapt to situations
12. VFE enables surprise prediction for active inference

